  <!-- ─── STEP 4: AI Prompt ─── -->
  <div class="step-card">
    <div class="time-badge">⏱ 20 min</div>
    <div class="step-card-header">
      <div class="step-num-big">4</div>
      <div>
        <div class="step-card-title">Configure the AI Classification Prompt</div>
        <div class="step-card-sub">The brain of the system — paste this exactly into your OpenAI HTTP module</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <p>In Module 2 (the HTTP request to OpenAI), your request body should look like this. Copy the system prompt below into the <strong>system</strong> message field:</p>
      <div class="prompt-box"><span class="label">System Prompt → OpenAI GPT-4o / GPT-4o Mini</span>You are a lead classifier for a small business WhatsApp inbox.

Analyse the incoming customer message and return ONLY a JSON object:
{
  "intent": "buy" | "price" | "support" | "spam",
  "confidence": 0.0–1.0,
  "hot_lead": true | false,
  "summary": "One sentence summary of what the customer wants",
  "suggested_reply": "A warm, professional reply under 160 characters"
}

Rules:
- "buy" = ready to purchase, asking about availability, "I want to order"
- "price" = asking about cost, packages, discounts — potential buyer
- "support" = existing customer with an issue or question
- "spam" = promotional, irrelevant, or gibberish
- hot_lead = true only when intent is "buy" AND confidence >= 0.8

Respond ONLY with valid JSON. No preamble. No explanation.</div>

      <p><strong>OpenAI HTTP request settings to use in Make.com:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>URL:</strong> https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions</li>
        <li><strong>Method:</strong> POST</li>
        <li><strong>Header:</strong> Authorization: Bearer &lt;your OpenAI API key&gt;</li>
        <li><strong>Body type:</strong> Raw → JSON</li>
        <li><strong>model:</strong> "gpt-4o-mini" (cheapest, fast) or "gpt-4o" (most accurate)</li>
        <li><strong>temperature:</strong> 0.2 (keeps output consistent)</li>
        <li><strong>max_tokens:</strong> 300</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top: 10px;">In Module 3 (JSON Parse), map <code style="background: var(--surface-2); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px;">{{intent}}</code>, <code style="background: var(--surface-2); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px;">{{hot_lead}}</code>, and <code style="background: var(--surface-2); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px;">{{suggested_reply}}</code> to drive the Router.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

