  <!-- INTENT CLASSIFICATION -->
  <div class="section-label">
    <div class="section-num">3</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">How AI Classifies Intent</h2>
  </div>
  <p style="font-size:14px; color: var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom: 16px;">The system recognises 4 message intents and routes each to a different action.</p>

  <div class="intent-grid">
    <div class="intent-card buy">
      <div class="intent-tag">🔥 Buy Intent</div>
      <div class="intent-title">Ready to Purchase</div>
      <div class="intent-desc">Messages like: "I want to order", "Do you have X available?", "How do I buy?", "Can I place an order?"</div>
      <div class="intent-action">→ Qualify + Alert Owner</div>
    </div>
    <div class="intent-card price">
      <div class="intent-tag">💰 Price Inquiry</div>
      <div class="intent-title">Asking About Cost</div>
      <div class="intent-desc">Messages like: "How much is X?", "What's your pricing?", "Do you offer discounts for bulk?"</div>
      <div class="intent-action">→ Qualify + Log Lead</div>
    </div>
    <div class="intent-card support">
      <div class="intent-tag">🛠 Support</div>
      <div class="intent-title">Existing Customer Issue</div>
      <div class="intent-desc">Messages like: "My order hasn't arrived", "I got the wrong item", "How do I return this?"</div>
      <div class="intent-action">→ Route to Support Queue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="intent-card spam">
      <div class="intent-tag">🚫 Spam / Irrelevant</div>
      <div class="intent-title">Not a Lead</div>
      <div class="intent-desc">Promotional messages, gibberish, wrong numbers, broadcast forwards, solicitations.</div>
      <div class="intent-action">→ Log Only, No Reply</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- HOT LEAD ALERTS -->
  <div class="section-label">
    <div class="section-num">4</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Hot Lead Alert Rules (When You Get Notified)</h2>
  </div>
  <p style="font-size:14px; color: var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom: 16px;">You shouldn't be pinged for every message — only the ones that matter.</p>

  <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 8px 24px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
    <div class="alert-rule">
      <div class="alert-dot hot"></div>
      <div>
        <div class="rule-title">🔴 Instant Alert — Send Now</div>
        <div class="rule-desc">Intent = "buy" AND confidence ≥ 0.8. This person is ready to purchase. You get a Slack ping / email with their number, message summary, and a direct link to open the chat.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="alert-rule">
      <div class="alert-dot warm"></div>
      <div>
        <div class="rule-title">🟡 Daily Digest — Price Inquiries</div>
        <div class="rule-desc">Intent = "price". Compiled into a daily email at 8am with all price inquiries from the last 24 hours. Includes AI-generated summary per lead.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="alert-rule">
      <div class="alert-dot"></div>
      <div>
        <div class="rule-title">🟢 No Alert — Check Sheet When Ready</div>
        <div class="rule-desc">Intent = "support" or "spam". Logged to Google Sheets. The support team reviews the support queue. Spam is filtered, not shown.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Pro tip:</strong> In Make.com, use a <strong>Filter</strong> module before the alert step: only continue if <code>{{hot_lead}} = true</code>. This prevents alert fatigue completely.
  </div>

