    <h2 class="section-title">Troubleshooting &amp; FAQs</h2>
  </div>

  <div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">WhatsApp messages aren't hitting my Make.com webhook</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Double-check that you subscribed to the "messages" field in Meta's Webhook configuration panel. Make sure the webhook URL is publicly accessible and that your Make.com scenario is in "Run Once" listening mode when you test. If Meta says "verification failed", check that your scenario has actually been saved and activated.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">OpenAI keeps returning invalid JSON or extra text</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Ensure "Respond ONLY with valid JSON. No preamble. No explanation." is the last line of your system prompt. Also set temperature to 0.2 and max_tokens to 300. In Make.com, use the JSON → Parse JSON module after the HTTP call rather than manually extracting text — it handles edge cases cleanly.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">The AI is misclassifying some intents — e.g. marking a buyer as "price"</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Add 2–3 example messages per intent to the system prompt as few-shot examples (e.g. "Example buy message: 'I want to order 10 units of product A'"). You can also lower the hot_lead confidence threshold from 0.8 to 0.7 if you're missing genuine buyers. Review your Google Sheet weekly and spot-check confidence scores.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Can I use this with my existing CRM instead of Google Sheets?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Yes. Make.com has native modules for HubSpot, Zoho, Pipedrive, Salesforce, and Airtable. Replace the Google Sheets module with your CRM's "Create Contact" or "Create Lead" module and map the same fields from the OpenAI JSON output.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Will customers know they're talking to a bot?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Not by default — the replies are designed to sound human and warm. You can optionally add a closing line like "A member of our team will follow up shortly!" if you prefer transparency, which is often a trust-builder for small businesses anyway.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">What does this cost to run per month?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Make.com free tier handles ~1,000 operations/month (suitable for testing). The Core plan at $9/month covers 10,000 operations, which handles roughly 1,400+ WhatsApp messages per month (each message uses ~7 operations). OpenAI GPT-4o Mini costs approximately $0.001 per classification. At 500 messages/month, total running cost is under $10/month.</div>
    </div>
